President Obama has announced his intention to nominate Father Pius Pietrzyk to the Board of Directors of the Legal Services Corporation. Father Pius is currently studying at the Pontifical University of St. Thomas Aquinas in Rome and serving at the Basilica of San Clemente. He has previously served as a Parochial Vicar in Ohio and has been a member of the Board of Directors of the Legal Services Corporation since 2010. Father Pius has also worked as a pro bono attorney with Immigration Services of the Catholic Charities of New York and as an attorney with Sidley & Austin. He holds a B.A. from the University of Arizona, a J.D. from the University of Chicago, and S.T.B./M.Div and S.T.L degrees from the Pontifical Faculty of the Immaculate Conception in Washington, DC.